--

To create a Class, we use the **`class`** keyword. A class name should always start with an uppercase letter.

```java
class Rectangle {
    int width;
    int height;
}
```
Now we can create an object of this class and set values for the attributes width and height.

```java
class Seedit {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Rectangle rectangle = new Rectangle(); 
        rectangle.width = 5.0;
        rectangle.height = 3.0;
        System.out.println("Width: " + rectangle.width);
        System.out.println("Height: " + rectangle.height);
    }
}
```

The third line of this snippet creates an object "rectangle" of the class "Rectangle".
We use the dot operator (.) to access the attributes of a class.

